author_ssm: Lena Evers-Hillstrom and Michael Chui, under the supervision of Maggie Schreiner and John Zarrillo
abstract_ssm: The Brooklyn Historical Society vertical files is an artificial collection compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff. The collection contains pamphlets, cards, advertisements, newspaper articles, magazines, letters, and more dating roughly from 1770 to the present documenting New York City and Long Island. This collection also includes biographical files on notable Brooklyn individuals.
